Stocks Decline; FTSE 100 Index Slips as Cairn Slides After Quitting Well

-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-09-13T07:57:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-13/stocks-decline-ftse-100-index-slips-as-cairn-slides-after-quitting-well.html
U.K. stocks fell, erasing earlier
gains, led by a selloff in  Cairn Energy Plc. (CNE)   The FTSE 100 Index lost 0.3 percent to 5,113.74 at 8:55
a.m. in  London  after earlier rallying as much as 1.3 percent.  Cairn dropped 8.5 percent to 286.1 pence after the Scottish
oil company focusing on Greenland abandoned its second well in
less than two months.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sarah Jones at 
 sjones35@bloomberg.net  